dict.string: sudo apt update && sudo apt dist-upgrade -y && sudo apt autoremove -y

kubectl get pods --all-namespaces -o json | jq '.items[] | select(.status.reason!=null) | select(.status.reason | contains("Evicted")) | "kubectl delete pods \(.metadata.name) -n \(.metadata.namespace)"'| xargs -n 1 bash -c
echo '{"apiVersion":"v1","kind":"Service","metadata":{"name":"tst"},"spec":{"clusterIP":"1.1.1.1","ports":[{"port":443}]}}' | kubectl apply -f - 2>&1 | sed 's/.*valid IPs is //'
sudo apt update && sudo apt-get -s dist-upgrade | grep "^Inst" | grep -i securi | awk -F " " {'print $2'} | sudo xargs apt-get install

kubectl get secret dispatcher-user-credentials -n rabbitmq -ojson | jq 'del(.metadata.namespace,.metadata.resourceVersion,.metadata.uid,.metadata.annotations,.metadata.ownerReferences,.metadata.selfLink) | .metadata.creationTimestamp=null' | kubectl apply -f -
